      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "See no reason to jump off TOPMOST (3) who won well over this track and distance last time out, positively ridden and coming away to score by 1.3 lengths. Stays in BM62 grade and gets in well after the claim. Lamont takes off 4kg, if she can keep it simple and sit outside the lead, the horse can do the rest. MONGOLIAN MISSION (7) is racing well without winning this campaign, not far away in tougher 3yo company at Sandown Lakeside when last seen. The $2.80 SP against Zakouma prior is a good little pointer. TITAN OF CHOICE (2) is going well, placing in his past couple, working home nicely behind a handy one at Pakenham last start. Up to 1500m now can suit. STAY SILENT (1) was no match for a dominant winner last time at Warrnambool but is racing fairly well and maps nicely. PAPAL ARMY (4) resumes and can sprint well.",
